with high hit point mobs and high mana usage/low damage output for Lures in Velious and we can see the problems arising. Wizard effectiveness in the 50+ game drops like a rock on the continent.<br><br>Remedies to these combinations of high hitpoints, high resistances, high mana usage/low damage for lures are not adequately addressed in the original line of Velious spells for Wizards. We were (and are) expected to continue with the original Kunark line of Lure spells with the addition of a lower 44th lvl one (Enticement of Flame). Enter the Bane spells, which are reportedly unresistable, do significant damage and at moderate mana cost (400). Following this logic we should consider Banes extremely high level Lures since their premise is the same. <br><br>Balance thoughts following Verant logic:<br><br>Making Lures more effective for Velious mobs say by decreasing mana usage or damage total will upset the balance of the 50+ Kunark game.<br>Lowering resist rates for 50+ mobs in Velious and Kunark will make all casters more effective, not just wizards, upsetting the 50+ game everywhere.<br><br>My suggestion considering these two problems is that Verant should make the Lure lines more of an inherent Wizard ability and examine the impact this will have on 50+ Kunark and Velious encounters, which I believe will be to make the Wizard more of an asset than a liability on both continents. What do I mean by inherent? In the current Lure spell line, the mana/damage ratio is very low which makes me believe that casting these spells is Difficult for a wizard. Why is that? Perhaps an enchanter or mage might find this kind of spell difficult but to Wizards this should be innate. Since the wizard is master of offensive spells, ramp up damage to mana in line with other wizard spells. Since the Lure line is the only direct damage line of spells the wizard gets post 50, it is by default the preferred attack spell.<br>Thus:<br>44th lvl: Enticement of Flame <br>DD Fire 360: mana 180 ratio 2:1<br>52nd lvl:  Lure of Frost <br>DD Cold 640: mana 260 ratio 2.5:1<br>55th lvl: Lure of Flame<br>DD Fire 1000: mana 360 ratio 2.75:1<br>58th lvl: Lure of Lightning<br>DD Magic 1360: mana 450 ratio 3:1<br>60th lvl Bane Spells<br>DD Magic 2000: mana 400 ratio 5:1<br>limited targets<br><br>Flames await :-))<br><br>Validata Tempestas<br>53rd Wizard<br>Guildmaster of the Company<br>Saryrn<br><br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uakailen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akailen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/01 3:51:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Not a flame! :)</span><hr size=1> Greetings!<br><br>Okay, one question I have is:  Aren't draughts considered DD?  I know wizards get them post 50, but you stated that Lures are the only DD spells wizards get post 50.<br><br>I like the idea someone (can't remember the name sorry!) said about having Lures unresistable if you use the correct Lure.  Correct meaning that if a mob is more resistant to magic and ice, then a fire based Lure should hit for full damage every cast.  I like your idea of improving the efficiency though.<br><br>Akailen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvinarruinthang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vinar Ruinthang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/01 5:59:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not a flame! :)</span><hr size=1> yes the draughts are dd and great spells if you are fighting in one of the 3 orignal contients.  Once you head over to velious draughts are resisted all the time.  And about enticement of flame.  I used that religiously for 2 weeks and after having over 70% of my casts resisted in velious ( yes a fire based lure against ice strong creatures resisted 70% of the time)  i gave up on it.  Lures were nerfed prematurely with the expansion of velious.  All our great spells are worthless when you only have 3 spells that hit at lvl 60. <p>Vinar Ruinthang<BR>Wizard of the 52nd Season<BR>Dread Overlord of the Violent Harvest</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/01 6:05:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=305.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question from an Enchanter...</span><hr size=1> The question was brought up at the Fan Faire by an enchanter about Velious Resistances.  The answer was simply &quot;We are reviewing the ENTIRE resistance scale of velious.  We see the problem.&quot;  Now I'm not sure if they were just refering to Enchanters or all classes with this kind of problem.  We can only hope.<br><br>W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=305.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgra